1
00:00:02,197 --> 00:00:03,461
Another three centimeters
to the right

2
00:00:03,499 --> 00:00:05,162
and you would have severed
your brachial artery.

3
00:00:05,203 --> 00:00:06,296
Autosuture, please.

4
00:00:06,339 --> 00:00:07,398
And if that had happened,

5
00:00:07,441 --> 00:00:09,434
you would have bled to death
right there in the holosuite.

6
00:00:10,548 --> 00:00:12,849
The human fascination
with "what might have been"

7
00:00:12,886 --> 00:00:14,081
is tiresome, Doctor.

8
00:00:14,123 --> 00:00:16,287
The artery is not severed
and I am not dead.

9
00:00:16,328 --> 00:00:18,195
Oh, well, forgive me
for boring you.

10
00:00:18,265 --> 00:00:19,529
Let me get straight
to the point.

11
00:00:19,567 --> 00:00:20,796
You're acting like a fool.

12
00:00:20,837 --> 00:00:23,172
Your observation is noted.

13
00:00:23,209 --> 00:00:25,874
But spending two years
in a Dominion prison camp

14
00:00:25,915 --> 00:00:27,441
has dulled my reflexes.

15
00:00:27,485 --> 00:00:29,615
This only proves that
I need further training.

16
00:00:29,657 --> 00:00:31,855
Turning off the holosuite
safety protocols

17
00:00:31,895 --> 00:00:34,492
during a battle simulation
is, at best, dubious.

18
00:00:34,534 --> 00:00:36,971
For a man with only one eye,
it's positively idiotic.

19
00:00:37,006 --> 00:00:39,705
Now, if you would consider
ocular replacement...

20
00:00:39,746 --> 00:00:42,685
I do not want
an artificial eye!

21
00:00:42,719 --> 00:00:45,384
Then you must accept the fact
that you have a disability

22
00:00:45,424 --> 00:00:46,517
and stop acting like...

23
00:00:46,561 --> 00:00:51,903
There are limits as to how far
I will indulge you, Doctor.

24
00:00:53,309 --> 00:00:54,744
General Martok, there is

25
00:00:54,779 --> 00:00:57,376
a priority message for you
from the Klingon High Council.

26
00:00:59,122 --> 00:01:00,523
We're done here.

27
00:01:00,558 --> 00:01:04,157
Route the message
to my quarters.

28
00:01:04,199 --> 00:01:05,326
Acknowledged.

29
00:01:05,368 --> 00:01:07,862
Doctor... thank you.

30
00:01:07,907 --> 00:01:09,342
If you really
want to thank me

31
00:01:09,377 --> 00:01:11,244
don't walk in here
dripping blood anymore.

32
00:01:11,314 --> 00:01:13,341
It takes days to get it
out of the carpet.

33
00:01:25,947 --> 00:01:27,416
Check it now.

34
00:01:29,021 --> 00:01:32,188
Still no increase in phaser
relay efficiency, sir.

35
00:01:32,228 --> 00:01:35,463
The through-put reading
is steady at 148.7.

36
00:01:35,501 --> 00:01:38,872
Have you initialized
the interface program?

37
00:01:38,909 --> 00:01:41,039
Yes, and then I charged
the prefire chamber

38
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:42,845
and recalibrated
the emitter stage.

39
00:01:42,884 --> 00:01:44,980
This thing just doesn't work!

40
00:01:45,022 --> 00:01:46,047
Sir.

41
00:01:47,661 --> 00:01:49,324
Very well.

42
00:01:49,432 --> 00:01:50,958
We'll start over.

43
00:01:51,002 --> 00:01:52,301
Go to the Engine Room

44
00:01:52,339 --> 00:01:53,808
and download
the operating system

45
00:01:53,841 --> 00:01:55,140
into the computer core

46
00:01:55,178 --> 00:01:57,809
but, this time,
do it one file at a time.

47
00:01:59,922 --> 00:02:01,448
Aye, sir.

48
00:02:04,198 --> 00:02:05,724
Good evening, General.

49
00:02:05,768 --> 00:02:06,861
Cadet.

50
00:02:06,904 --> 00:02:08,237
General.

51
00:02:10,344 --> 00:02:13,043
I did not expect you
until 2200 hours.

52
00:02:13,084 --> 00:02:15,282
I must cancel our appointment.

53
00:02:15,322 --> 00:02:17,053
I've received new orders
from the High Council...

54
00:02:17,092 --> 00:02:18,823
a mission of some importance.

55
00:02:18,863 --> 00:02:19,956
I must prepare.

56
00:02:19,999 --> 00:02:21,126
Of course.

57
00:02:21,168 --> 00:02:23,662
May glory and honor
follow you on your journey.

58
00:02:24,676 --> 00:02:26,772
Ah... excuse me, sirs?

59
00:02:26,814 --> 00:02:29,912
Could I just slip by?

60
00:02:36,903 --> 00:02:38,372
How is the shoulder?

61
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:42,141
Oh, Dr. Bashir made
the necessary repairs.

62
00:02:42,181 --> 00:02:44,117
I told him it was
a holosuite accident.

63
00:02:44,152 --> 00:02:46,054
He would not understand
the need to draw blood

64
00:02:46,090 --> 00:02:48,584
in a warrior's
training exercise.

65
00:02:48,629 --> 00:02:49,996
Few humans would.

66
00:02:50,032 --> 00:02:54,269
However, I do apologize again
for the inconvenience.

67
00:02:54,308 --> 00:02:56,175
I did not intend
to cause so much damage.

68
00:02:56,212 --> 00:02:59,708
I was the one who did not
parry the blow in time.

69
00:02:59,753 --> 00:03:01,986
A simple, foolish mistake

70
00:03:02,025 --> 00:03:03,927
one that I would not have made
two years ago.

71
00:03:03,962 --> 00:03:06,058
Can you discuss the mission?

72
00:03:08,004 --> 00:03:12,173
Three days ago,
the Battle Cruiser <i>B'Moth</i>

73
00:03:12,213 --> 00:03:15,380
began a patrol
along the Cardassian border.

74
00:03:15,454 --> 00:03:18,894
They have not been
heard from since.

75
00:03:18,928 --> 00:03:21,126
They are now reported
as missing.

76
00:03:21,167 --> 00:03:24,504
It is possible she was
destroyed by the Dominion.

77
00:03:24,541 --> 00:03:27,138
The Jem'Hadar attacked
a Federation starship

78
00:03:27,180 --> 00:03:28,774
near the border
less than a week ago.

79
00:03:28,817 --> 00:03:31,847
That is our assumption
as well, but we must be sure.

80
00:03:31,890 --> 00:03:33,723
So I have been given command

81
00:03:33,761 --> 00:03:36,962
of a bird-of-prey...
the <i>Rotarran...</i>

82
00:03:37,001 --> 00:03:38,800
to conduct a search
for the <i>B'Moth.</i>

83
00:03:38,839 --> 00:03:40,331
This is the first time

84
00:03:40,375 --> 00:03:44,146
I will have led troops
in the field since...

85
00:03:44,184 --> 00:03:47,180
my confinement by the Dominion.

86
00:03:47,224 --> 00:03:49,457
It must be an exciting prospect.

87
00:03:49,496 --> 00:03:52,435
I tell you, Worf...
without shame...

88
00:03:52,469 --> 00:03:55,202
there were days
in that prison camp

89
00:03:55,242 --> 00:03:57,770
when the thought that
I would never again

90
00:03:57,814 --> 00:04:03,053
set foot in a Klingon vessel
made me weep like an old woman.

91
00:04:03,092 --> 00:04:05,996
I envy you the days ahead.

92
00:04:06,032 --> 00:04:08,002
It will be a glorious adventure.

93
00:04:08,036 --> 00:04:12,741
An adventure that we
could share, my friend.

94
00:04:12,780 --> 00:04:15,753
I need someone I can
trust at my side

95
00:04:15,787 --> 00:04:18,350
someone whose loyalty
I can count on.

96
00:04:19,996 --> 00:04:22,297
Worf, son of Mogh

97
00:04:22,334 --> 00:04:25,466
I ask you to join me
on this mission

98
00:04:25,508 --> 00:04:27,307
as my friend...

99
00:04:27,345 --> 00:04:30,341
and as my First Officer.

100
00:06:33,081 --> 00:06:35,518
I've told the General
that I'm inclined

101
00:06:35,554 --> 00:06:38,755
to grant his request
for your services, Commander.

102
00:06:38,794 --> 00:06:41,790
I can certainly understand
why he wants you along.

103
00:06:41,835 --> 00:06:43,361
You're a fine officer.

104
00:06:43,405 --> 00:06:44,566
But I'm not sure

105
00:06:44,607 --> 00:06:46,668
why you want to go
on this mission.

106
00:06:46,711 --> 00:06:47,940
It is a great honor

107
00:06:47,981 --> 00:06:50,452
to be asked to serve
under General Martok.

108
00:06:50,486 --> 00:06:54,757
And he saved my life
in the Dominion prison camp.

109
00:06:54,796 --> 00:06:57,233
Oh? You didn't put that
in your mission report.

110
00:06:57,268 --> 00:06:59,295
It was a personal matter.

111
00:06:59,340 --> 00:07:01,641
Not something that belongs
in an official report.

112
00:07:01,677 --> 00:07:03,271
Go on.

113
00:07:03,314 --> 00:07:05,307
You know that I was
forced to fight

114
00:07:05,353 --> 00:07:07,289
the Jem'Hadar guards
in the camp.

115
00:07:07,323 --> 00:07:09,259
Each day they would
call me to the ring

116
00:07:09,295 --> 00:07:10,958
and each day I would fight

117
00:07:10,999 --> 00:07:15,965
but then there came a day
when I... wavered.

118
00:07:16,010 --> 00:07:18,811
You mean you didn't want
to go back into the ring?

119
00:07:18,849 --> 00:07:21,913
No. I mean I considered
letting them kill me.

120
00:07:21,956 --> 00:07:24,223
It seemed like the only way out.

121
00:07:24,260 --> 00:07:25,820
Just before I went into the ring

122
00:07:25,864 --> 00:07:27,994
Martok turned to wish me success

123
00:07:28,036 --> 00:07:29,665
and then he saw
what I was planning...

124
00:07:29,706 --> 00:07:31,642
he saw it in my eyes.

125
00:07:31,677 --> 00:07:34,012
It was a moment of <i>tova'dok.</i>

126
00:07:34,049 --> 00:07:35,348
Of what?

127
00:07:35,385 --> 00:07:38,084
There is no human word for it.

128
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:41,393
It is a moment of... clarity

129
00:07:41,432 --> 00:07:43,801
between two warriors
on a field of battle.

130
00:07:43,837 --> 00:07:45,830
Much is said
without the need for words.

131
00:07:45,874 --> 00:07:49,245
In that moment,
he knew what was in my mind.

132
00:07:49,282 --> 00:07:52,278
Once I realized that he saw
my intention to give up

133
00:07:52,322 --> 00:07:54,520
I could no longer
go through with it.

134
00:07:54,561 --> 00:07:57,534
I went back into the ring
and fought once more.

135
00:07:57,633 --> 00:08:00,597
He had given me
his warrior's heart.

136
00:08:03,570 --> 00:08:06,634
Perhaps it is something
a human cannot understand.

137
00:08:12,156 --> 00:08:14,058
As of this moment

138
00:08:14,093 --> 00:08:16,462
you are relieved
of all Starfleet obligations

139
00:08:16,498 --> 00:08:18,491
and placed on detached service

140
00:08:18,537 --> 00:08:20,974
to the Imperial Klingon
Defense Forces.

141
00:08:23,614 --> 00:08:25,778
Thank you, sir.

142
00:08:25,819 --> 00:08:27,311
Mr. Worf.

143
00:08:30,028 --> 00:08:31,429
<i>Qapla'!</i>

144
00:08:32,768 --> 00:08:34,169
<i>Qapla'!</i>

145
00:08:53,246 --> 00:08:55,182
The revised duty roster.

146
00:08:55,216 --> 00:08:56,981
Read it and weep.

147
00:08:57,021 --> 00:08:59,754
Small arms recalibration?

148
00:08:59,794 --> 00:09:01,491
Does that mean all
the small arms on the station?

149
00:09:01,531 --> 00:09:02,499
Afraid so.

150
00:09:02,533 --> 00:09:05,164
And I need an experienced
combat officer to do it.

151
00:09:05,205 --> 00:09:06,606
Worf has already set up
the parameters.

152
00:09:06,642 --> 00:09:08,407
All you need to do
is just make sure it gets done.

153
00:09:08,445 --> 00:09:10,882
I'm the new
Intelligence Officer?

154
00:09:12,721 --> 00:09:14,190
It has to be a Starfleet officer

155
00:09:14,225 --> 00:09:15,785
with a level-4
security clearance.

156
00:09:15,829 --> 00:09:17,196
That means either you or Dax

157
00:09:17,232 --> 00:09:20,171
and I need Dax to take over
as Fleet Liaison Officer.

158
00:09:20,205 --> 00:09:21,469
Beats retuning phaser rifles.

159
00:09:21,508 --> 00:09:24,275
Well, I certainly hope
Worf's enjoying himself

160
00:09:24,314 --> 00:09:27,150
while we're stuck here
taking over his duties.

161
00:09:27,187 --> 00:09:29,954
Julian, have you ever been
on a Klingon ship?

162
00:09:29,993 --> 00:09:32,430
If you think the <i>Defiant</i>
is cramped and uncomfortable

163
00:09:32,465 --> 00:09:34,732
try spending a week
on a bird-of-prey.

164
00:09:34,770 --> 00:09:37,241
Worf isn't exactly
taking a luxury cruise.

165
00:09:37,276 --> 00:09:38,609
Serving on a Klingon ship

166
00:09:38,646 --> 00:09:40,947
is like being with a gang
of ancient sea pirates.

167
00:09:40,984 --> 00:09:43,888
You advance in rank by
killing the people above you.

168
00:09:43,924 --> 00:09:44,983
So everywhere you turn

169
00:09:45,026 --> 00:09:46,757
you're surrounded
by potential assassins.

170
00:09:46,796 --> 00:09:47,764
Well, that's crazy.

171
00:09:47,799 --> 00:09:48,994
How can a ship
function like that?

172
00:09:49,035 --> 00:09:50,902
It's not quite that chaotic.

173
00:09:50,939 --> 00:09:53,433
The social and military
hierarchy of a Klingon vessel

174
00:09:53,478 --> 00:09:55,107
is very strictly enforced.

175
00:09:55,215 --> 00:09:58,882
A subordinate can only
challenge a direct superior

176
00:09:58,924 --> 00:10:00,119
and only under
certain conditions.

177
00:10:00,226 --> 00:10:02,561
What sort of "conditions"?

178
00:10:02,598 --> 00:10:04,591
Dereliction of duty

179
00:10:04,636 --> 00:10:07,803
dishonorable conduct,
cowardice...

180
00:10:07,843 --> 00:10:10,144
Cowardice? A Klingon?

181
00:10:10,214 --> 00:10:11,478
It's been known to happen.

182
00:10:11,518 --> 00:10:13,921
The Klingons are
as diverse a people as any.

183
00:10:13,957 --> 00:10:16,155
Some of them are strong,
and some of them are weak.

184
00:10:16,195 --> 00:10:18,062
I'd say those two

185
00:10:18,099 --> 00:10:21,402
definitely fall
into the strong category.

186
00:10:35,504 --> 00:10:37,030
Trouble?

187
00:10:37,074 --> 00:10:38,167
Not yet.

188
00:10:38,210 --> 00:10:39,975
I can see why they
caught your attention.

189
00:10:40,014 --> 00:10:41,313
Are they off Martok's new ship?

190
00:10:41,350 --> 00:10:43,217
Just docked.

191
00:10:43,287 --> 00:10:44,881
They seem quiet enough.

192
00:10:44,924 --> 00:10:47,327
For the moment, maybe

193
00:10:47,363 --> 00:10:49,926
but you see the one on the left
wearing the necklace?

194
00:10:49,969 --> 00:10:51,495
Yes.

195
00:10:51,539 --> 00:10:53,008
Those are neck bones...

196
00:10:53,043 --> 00:10:54,603
Cardassian neck bones.

197
00:11:01,093 --> 00:11:03,428
Decided not to wear
the sash after all?

198
00:11:03,465 --> 00:11:05,993
Officially, there is no
House of Mogh in the Empire

199
00:11:06,037 --> 00:11:07,027
so I saw little point

200
00:11:07,074 --> 00:11:09,044
in wearing its emblem
on a Klingon ship.

201
00:11:09,078 --> 00:11:11,048
How do you think
the crew's going to feel

202
00:11:11,082 --> 00:11:13,143
about serving under a man
without a House?

203
00:11:13,187 --> 00:11:15,351
How they feel is unimportant.

204
00:11:15,391 --> 00:11:18,489
All I require from them
is obedience.

205
00:11:18,531 --> 00:11:21,094
Spoken like an uncaring,
hard-nosed autocrat...

206
00:11:21,137 --> 00:11:23,039
the quintessential
First Officer.

207
00:11:24,946 --> 00:11:27,919
I-I do not wish
to have a lengthy good-bye.

208
00:11:27,953 --> 00:11:30,983
I wasn't planning
on having one.

209
00:11:31,025 --> 00:11:32,358
Good.

210
00:11:44,088 --> 00:11:45,283
Jadzia.

211
00:11:45,357 --> 00:11:46,917
Yes.

212
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,293
I think it would be better

213
00:11:48,330 --> 00:11:50,266
to part company
here on the station.

214
00:11:50,301 --> 00:11:51,793
Oh, I'm coming with you.

215
00:11:51,838 --> 00:11:53,205
What?

216
00:11:53,241 --> 00:11:55,234
The <i>Rotarran</i> is shorthanded

217
00:11:55,279 --> 00:11:57,648
and I still have
four months leave coming.

218
00:11:57,684 --> 00:12:00,281
And I've already cleared it
with Martok and Benjamin.

219
00:12:00,323 --> 00:12:01,883
I'm your new Science Officer.

220
00:12:01,927 --> 00:12:04,057
Why did you not tell me?

221
00:12:04,098 --> 00:12:05,829
It's more fun this way.

222
00:12:05,869 --> 00:12:07,566
And after getting a good look

223
00:12:07,606 --> 00:12:10,237
at a couple members
of the <i>Rotarran's</i> crew

224
00:12:10,278 --> 00:12:13,479
I don't think we're going
to be having a lot of fun

225
00:12:13,519 --> 00:12:15,318
on this mission.

226
00:12:36,403 --> 00:12:37,371
Boo!

227
00:12:42,182 --> 00:12:46,283
<i>Ros-te-ka cha'Domak</i>
<i>ootha Trill?</i>

228
00:12:46,324 --> 00:12:48,557
I am Tavana,
Engineering Officer.

229
00:12:48,596 --> 00:12:50,931
I'm Jadzia Dax, Science Officer.

230
00:12:50,968 --> 00:12:52,335
Dax?

231
00:12:52,371 --> 00:12:54,501
Are you related
to the great Curzon Dax?

232
00:12:54,542 --> 00:12:56,911
Curzon was the last host
for my symbiont.

233
00:12:56,947 --> 00:12:58,176
I carry his memories.

234
00:12:58,217 --> 00:12:59,185
Ah!

235
00:12:59,219 --> 00:13:04,060
My mother met the great Curzon
on the Homeworld once.

236
00:13:04,097 --> 00:13:06,261
She said he was
very taken with her.

237
00:13:06,301 --> 00:13:10,538
Curzon was very "taken"
with many people.

238
00:13:10,578 --> 00:13:12,445
So was my mother.

239
00:13:25,477 --> 00:13:27,812
I am Worf, son of Mogh.

240
00:13:27,849 --> 00:13:32,622
I now take my place
as First Officer.

241
00:13:32,659 --> 00:13:36,258
I serve the Captain,
but I stand for the crew.

242
00:13:37,637 --> 00:13:40,974
Who brings the record of battle
for this ship?

243
00:13:51,935 --> 00:13:54,168
I, Kornan, son of Shovak

244
00:13:54,207 --> 00:13:56,040
Weapon's Officer
of the ship of <i>Rotarran</i>

245
00:13:56,077 --> 00:13:57,808
present the glorious record
of our honor

246
00:13:57,848 --> 00:14:00,319
and hope that you may find us
worthy of your leadership.

247
00:14:07,001 --> 00:14:09,199
If you're looking for victories,
you won't find any.

248
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:11,711
Not for the last seven months.

249
00:14:11,745 --> 00:14:16,119
I do not need help recognizing
a list of failures.

250
00:14:19,529 --> 00:14:21,396
It is clear to me

251
00:14:21,433 --> 00:14:25,374
that none of you are worthy
of my blood or my life.

252
00:14:26,745 --> 00:14:29,273
But I will stand for you

253
00:14:29,317 --> 00:14:32,415
and together, we will restore
honor to this ship

254
00:14:32,458 --> 00:14:34,895
and bring glory to the Empire.

255
00:14:45,286 --> 00:14:46,721
Ah...

256
00:14:52,034 --> 00:14:54,198
I have accepted
the crew's battle records

257
00:14:54,239 --> 00:14:57,040
and on their behalf,
I pledge you our lives

258
00:14:57,078 --> 00:15:00,381
and ask that you lead us
as Commander of this ship.

259
00:15:05,129 --> 00:15:09,628
I accept your lives
into my hands.

260
00:15:09,672 --> 00:15:11,266
<i>De-lak DoH!</i>

261
00:15:12,311 --> 00:15:14,372
Clear all moorings.

262
00:15:14,416 --> 00:15:15,680
Release docking clamps.

263
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:17,587
Docking clamps released.

264
00:15:17,624 --> 00:15:19,594
Bow thrusters ahead
one half.

265
00:15:21,164 --> 00:15:23,260
We have cleared
the docking ring.

266
00:15:23,303 --> 00:15:26,276
Ahead one-quarter impulse.

267
00:15:30,886 --> 00:15:32,822
Helmsman, plot a direct course

268
00:15:32,857 --> 00:15:35,658
to the last known position
of the <i>B'Moth,</i> maximum warp.

269
00:15:35,696 --> 00:15:38,532
No. That would take us
through the Tong Beak Nebula.

270
00:15:38,569 --> 00:15:40,334
I want to go around the nebula.

271
00:15:40,373 --> 00:15:43,346
General, that will add
a full day to our journey.

272
00:15:43,380 --> 00:15:44,849
I'm aware of that.

273
00:15:44,884 --> 00:15:46,649
There are reports
of the Dominion

274
00:15:46,688 --> 00:15:48,317
operating ships in the nebula.

275
00:15:48,358 --> 00:15:50,955
I would like to avoid
a fight with the Jem'Hadar.

276
00:15:52,266 --> 00:15:54,931
You wish to... avoid a fight?

277
00:15:55,941 --> 00:16:00,042
Your tone does not sit well
with me, Helmsman.

278
00:16:01,319 --> 00:16:03,882
Our mission
is to find the <i>B'Moth</i>

279
00:16:03,925 --> 00:16:06,378
not to satisfy
your warrior's pride.

280
00:16:06,511 --> 00:16:08,276
My apologies, sir.

281
00:16:08,316 --> 00:16:10,617
I meant no disrespect.

282
00:16:10,654 --> 00:16:12,955
Then follow your orders
and lay in a course.

283
00:16:12,992 --> 00:16:14,256
Maximum warp.

284
00:16:14,296 --> 00:16:15,856
Yes, Commander.

285
00:16:15,899 --> 00:16:19,395
Maximum warp, around...

286
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:21,342
the nebula.

287
00:16:23,382 --> 00:16:25,113
Helm ready.

288
00:16:28,327 --> 00:16:29,956
