<i>Kol KeH less...</i>

300
00:17:37,846 --> 00:17:39,281
Maybe you didn't read

301
00:17:39,383 --> 00:17:42,788
the crew roster,
but my name is Dax

302
00:17:42,823 --> 00:17:45,294
and I'm the new Science Officer
on this garbage scow

303
00:17:45,396 --> 00:17:48,266
and you were in my seat.

304
00:17:50,206 --> 00:17:52,677
I'm glad we understand
each other.

305
00:17:52,712 --> 00:17:55,183
Now get... down
to the other end

306
00:17:55,217 --> 00:17:56,709
where you belong.

307
00:18:01,832 --> 00:18:03,768
Stewed bok-rat liver?

308
00:18:03,803 --> 00:18:05,864
It's not very fresh.

309
00:18:05,908 --> 00:18:09,974
With a little bloodwine,
it might be acceptable.

310
00:18:10,016 --> 00:18:14,117
Ha. There's been no bloodwine
on this ship for six months.

311
00:18:14,158 --> 00:18:15,491
Really?

312
00:18:15,528 --> 00:18:18,091
Then I'm glad
I brought three barrels aboard

313
00:18:18,134 --> 00:18:20,298
before we left Deep Space 9.

314
00:18:21,541 --> 00:18:23,944
Three barrels?

315
00:18:26,152 --> 00:18:27,985
"Dishonorable conduct.

316
00:18:28,022 --> 00:18:29,651
"Dereliction of duty.

317
00:18:29,693 --> 00:18:31,287
"Inattention to orders.

318
00:18:31,330 --> 00:18:32,765
"Unmotivated.

319
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:34,964
Insufficiently aggressive."

320
00:18:35,004 --> 00:18:39,036
These personnel reports
read like prison records.

321
00:18:39,080 --> 00:18:40,070
We should remember

322
00:18:40,116 --> 00:18:41,779
that the <i>Rotarran</i>
has been defeated

323
00:18:41,820 --> 00:18:43,346
again and again
by the Jem'Hadar.

324
00:18:43,457 --> 00:18:46,361
It is not surprising
the crew morale has suffered.

325
00:18:46,396 --> 00:18:49,335
It's more than a case
of low morale, Worf.

326
00:18:49,370 --> 00:18:52,137
This crew has been defeated
so many times

327
00:18:52,176 --> 00:18:56,709
they expect defeat,
and that is dangerous.

328
00:18:56,752 --> 00:18:58,882
They need a victory.

329
00:18:58,924 --> 00:19:00,951
One decisive battle
against the Jem'Hadar

330
00:19:00,995 --> 00:19:02,828
would do much
to lift their spirits.

331
00:19:04,202 --> 00:19:05,694
And mine.

332
00:19:09,046 --> 00:19:13,785
No one hungers
for a victory over the Jem'Hadar

333
00:19:13,823 --> 00:19:18,026
more than I do... no one...

334
00:19:18,066 --> 00:19:20,367
but we must be cautious.

335
00:19:20,404 --> 00:19:23,035
We cannot risk
taking this crew into combat

336
00:19:23,077 --> 00:19:24,376
before they're ready.

337
00:19:24,447 --> 00:19:25,882
They will be ready.

338
00:19:25,916 --> 00:19:27,385
I will see to that.

339
00:19:27,453 --> 00:19:29,320
I know you will, my friend.

340
00:19:29,358 --> 00:19:31,693
Together,
we will make the <i>Rotarran</i>

341
00:19:31,729 --> 00:19:35,396
an honorable ship again,
a ship worthy of the Empire.

342
00:19:35,437 --> 00:19:38,501
You may return
to your station.

343
00:19:44,557 --> 00:19:46,220
The Cardassians were trapped

344
00:19:46,261 --> 00:19:48,094
between us
and the asteroid field.

345
00:19:48,132 --> 00:19:49,259
It was perfect.

346
00:19:49,301 --> 00:19:50,530
Their power was failing.

347
00:19:50,570 --> 00:19:52,199
They had no other ships nearby

348
00:19:52,241 --> 00:19:54,234
and our weapons
were fully charged.

349
00:19:54,278 --> 00:19:57,649
And we were still denied
a victory.

350
00:19:57,687 --> 00:20:01,218
Three Jem'Hadar ships appeared
from out of the asteroid field.

351
00:20:01,261 --> 00:20:02,992
Three to one are long odds.

352
00:20:03,031 --> 00:20:04,796
I'd say you did well just...

353
00:20:04,835 --> 00:20:06,999
getting away
with your ship in one piece.

354
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:10,172
Getting away is something
we've become very good at.

355
00:20:10,214 --> 00:20:11,979
The <i>Rotarran</i>
can run away from battle

356
00:20:12,018 --> 00:20:13,817
faster than any ship
in the Quadrant.

357
00:20:13,855 --> 00:20:16,224
You never could handle
your bloodwine, Leskit.

358
00:20:16,260 --> 00:20:18,493
You sound
like a sniveling Ferengi

359
00:20:18,566 --> 00:20:20,331
crying about lost profit.

360
00:20:20,370 --> 00:20:22,864
That's supposed
to wound my pride

361
00:20:22,908 --> 00:20:24,878
but Tavana has forgotten

362
00:20:24,912 --> 00:20:27,281
that no one serving
on the <i>Rotarran</i>

363
00:20:27,318 --> 00:20:28,787
has any pride left.

364
00:20:28,821 --> 00:20:31,122
Does that include me?

365
00:20:33,364 --> 00:20:37,065
I do not wish to insult someone
who brought me wine

366
00:20:37,106 --> 00:20:39,475
but one does wonder

367
00:20:39,512 --> 00:20:42,451
why the successor
to the great Curzon Dax

368
00:20:42,484 --> 00:20:45,753
would consent to serve
upon a ship like this.

369
00:20:45,792 --> 00:20:47,352
It's no mystery.

370
00:20:47,395 --> 00:20:49,798
She's the <i>parmach'kai</i>
of our new First Officer.

371
00:20:49,834 --> 00:20:53,866
I heard it on the space station
before we left.

372
00:20:53,910 --> 00:20:56,746
Worf is only part
of the reason I'm here.

373
00:20:56,782 --> 00:21:00,587
I think it is an honor
to serve under General Martok.

374
00:21:00,624 --> 00:21:02,321
You mean the one-eyed giant?

375
00:21:03,397 --> 00:21:05,960
I wouldn't let him
hear you say that.

376
00:21:06,002 --> 00:21:07,403
He won't.

377
00:21:07,439 --> 00:21:10,070
Unless Worf is not the only one

378
00:21:10,112 --> 00:21:12,709
you're sharing a bed with
this trip.

379
00:21:12,750 --> 00:21:14,515
On this trip

380
00:21:14,555 --> 00:21:16,924
my bed is as empty as yours,
Leskit

381
00:21:16,961 --> 00:21:20,696
except mine is empty by choice.

382
00:21:22,405 --> 00:21:25,002
Now, that is a sound
I haven't heard

383
00:21:25,044 --> 00:21:27,140
on this ship for a long time.

384
00:21:27,183 --> 00:21:29,085
It won't last.

385
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:34,029
This ship is made for tears,
not laughter.

386
00:21:34,064 --> 00:21:37,060
You're really not much fun
at parties, are you, Kornan?

387
00:21:37,105 --> 00:21:38,904
Make your jokes.

388
00:21:38,942 --> 00:21:42,883
Hold off fate for another day
if you can

389
00:21:42,918 --> 00:21:48,386
but this ship and all the souls
within its hull are cursed.

390
00:21:48,429 --> 00:21:50,627
Death and dishonor

391
00:21:50,734 --> 00:21:53,205
walk these corridors
like members of the crew.

392
00:21:53,240 --> 00:21:55,142
Aw, you talk too much, Kornan.

393
00:21:55,177 --> 00:21:57,044
Tell me you
don't believe it, too.

394
00:21:59,286 --> 00:22:00,915
We've cloaked.

395
00:22:00,957 --> 00:22:03,053
Alert Status One.

396
00:22:03,095 --> 00:22:05,065
A Jem'Hadar patrol ship
is directly ahead.

397
00:22:05,099 --> 00:22:07,069
Prepare for combat operations.

398
00:22:10,645 --> 00:22:12,342
Now you will see.

399
00:22:12,382 --> 00:22:16,847
Either death or dishonor
will visit us this day

400
00:22:16,891 --> 00:22:20,524
and there will be nothing
that you or I

401
00:22:20,567 --> 00:22:23,038
or any of us can do about it.

402
00:22:33,328 --> 00:22:35,298
What are they doing here

403
00:22:35,332 --> 00:22:37,667
this far
from the Cardassian border?

404
00:22:37,737 --> 00:22:38,796
They're conducting

405
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:40,571
active polaron scans
of this sector.

406
00:22:40,611 --> 00:22:43,412
It's likely they're on some kind
of reconnaissance mission.

407
00:22:43,450 --> 00:22:45,887
Can their scans penetrate
our cloak?

408
00:22:45,922 --> 00:22:46,890
I'd say there's less

409
00:22:46,924 --> 00:22:48,689
than a three percent
chance of detection.

410
00:22:48,796 --> 00:22:50,265
What's our weapons status?

411
00:22:50,298 --> 00:22:52,200
Torpedo bays are loaded.
Warheads are armed.

412
00:22:52,236 --> 00:22:54,707
Disruptors are locked on target.

413
00:22:54,809 --> 00:22:55,640
They've increased speed.

414
00:22:55,677 --> 00:22:57,169
They're beginning to pull away.

415
00:22:57,214 --> 00:22:58,375
Shall I match velocity?

416
00:22:59,686 --> 00:23:00,813
No.

417
00:23:00,855 --> 00:23:03,520
Take us back
to our original course.

418
00:23:03,561 --> 00:23:07,228
Forgive this unworthy officer's
poor hearing

419
00:23:07,269 --> 00:23:09,068
but what was your order?

420
00:23:09,107 --> 00:23:11,544
Take us back
to our original course!

421
00:23:11,579 --> 00:23:15,178
Our priority
is to find the <i>B'Moth.</i>

422
00:23:20,732 --> 00:23:22,531
Sir, we have them in our sights.

423
00:23:22,569 --> 00:23:23,537
They cannot escape if...

424
00:23:23,571 --> 00:23:24,561
No, Worf.

425
00:23:24,608 --> 00:23:25,907
But letting the ship go...

426
00:23:25,943 --> 00:23:27,537
Do not question me!

427
00:23:29,084 --> 00:23:30,713
Is the course laid in?

428
00:23:30,754 --> 00:23:31,983
Yes, Captain.

429
00:23:32,023 --> 00:23:34,517
I await your next command.

430
00:23:34,562 --> 00:23:37,558
Engage.

431
00:23:45,754 --> 00:23:48,225
Stand down from Alert Status.

432
00:23:48,259 --> 00:23:50,092
You have the Bridge.

433
00:23:55,476 --> 00:23:56,809
Commander.

434
00:24:00,887 --> 00:24:02,143
That was a mistake.

435
00:24:02,276 --> 00:24:03,768
We shouldn't have let them go.

436
00:24:03,812 --> 00:24:08,049
Our orders are to find
the <i>B'Moth,</i> not seek combat.

437
00:24:08,089 --> 00:24:10,059
It was a prudent decision.

438
00:24:10,093 --> 00:24:11,790
To hell with prudence.

439
00:24:11,830 --> 00:24:13,493
This isn't
a Federation starship.

440
00:24:13,601 --> 00:24:15,434
This is a Klingon bird-of-prey.

441
00:24:15,471 --> 00:24:17,338
We could've had an easy victory

442
00:24:17,376 --> 00:24:20,713
and in case you haven't noticed,
this crew could use a victory.

443
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:22,185
Enough.

444
00:24:22,220 --> 00:24:23,188
You may be my <i>parmach'kai</i>

445
00:24:23,222 --> 00:24:24,623
but that does not
give you the right...

446
00:24:24,658 --> 00:24:27,323
I'm an officer on this ship

447
00:24:27,365 --> 00:24:29,232
and I am trying
to warn my superior

448
00:24:29,269 --> 00:24:31,740
that a dangerous situation
is developing

449
00:24:31,774 --> 00:24:34,337
and that he'd better
do something about it.

450
00:24:34,380 --> 00:24:36,908
What do you mean "dangerous"?

451
00:24:38,990 --> 00:24:41,757
Take a good look
around you, Commander.

452
00:24:41,796 --> 00:24:44,359
Maybe it's just me

453
00:24:44,402 --> 00:24:45,894
but I think we're in trouble.

454
00:24:57,998 --> 00:24:59,797
I brought you here to support me

455
00:24:59,836 --> 00:25:01,863
not to undermine my authority.

456
00:25:01,907 --> 00:25:05,005
I am simply trying to point out
that we had an opportunity

457
00:25:05,047 --> 00:25:08,543
to destroy an enemy ship
with little risk to ourselves.

458
00:25:08,588 --> 00:25:10,251
Little risk?

459
00:25:11,929 --> 00:25:14,560
What if they'd have gotten off
a distress call

460
00:25:14,601 --> 00:25:16,298
before we could destroy them?

461
00:25:16,338 --> 00:25:17,807
They could have given away
our position

462
00:25:17,842 --> 00:25:18,810
called in reinforcements.

463
00:25:18,844 --> 00:25:20,575
We would have spent
the next three days

464
00:25:20,682 --> 00:25:21,843
avoiding Jem'Hadar ships

465
00:25:21,884 --> 00:25:24,253
instead of carrying
out our mission.

466
00:25:24,289 --> 00:25:27,022
No, my friend.

467
00:25:27,062 --> 00:25:29,431
No...

468
00:25:29,467 --> 00:25:32,440
This was not the right time
for battle.

469
00:25:35,748 --> 00:25:39,883
You question my judgment
in this matter?

470
00:25:40,893 --> 00:25:42,453
No.

471
00:25:42,496 --> 00:25:43,623
Good.

472
00:25:43,698 --> 00:25:47,069
Without your support,
I cannot command this ship.

473
00:25:48,743 --> 00:25:50,770
Tell me...

474
00:25:50,815 --> 00:25:53,651
that I have not made a mistake

475
00:25:53,687 --> 00:25:55,554
in making you my First Officer.

476
00:25:55,591 --> 00:25:57,721
You have my full support,
General.

477
00:25:59,935 --> 00:26:02,600
I knew you would not fail me,
Worf

478
00:26:02,640 --> 00:26:07,105
and you can rest assured,
I will not fail you.

479
00:26:18,140 --> 00:26:21,841
Two years, I spent
on the Cardassian border.

480
00:26:21,883 --> 00:26:25,654
Two years fighting Guls
and Legates and Glinns.

481
00:26:25,725 --> 00:26:28,060
They were cunning enemies.

482
00:26:28,096 --> 00:26:29,793
Always had us chasing

483
00:26:29,834 --> 00:26:32,773
holo-projections
and sensor ghosts.

484
00:26:32,806 --> 00:26:35,676
Everything was a game with them.

485
00:26:35,713 --> 00:26:39,414
Always had a plan
within a plan within a plan

486
00:26:39,454 --> 00:26:41,584
leading to a trap.

487
00:26:41,626 --> 00:26:43,790
It was an honor to kill them.

488
00:26:45,167 --> 00:26:47,468
The Cardassians.

489
00:26:47,506 --> 00:26:48,701
Ah!

490
00:26:48,741 --> 00:26:51,908
But you can respect a Cardassian

491
00:26:51,949 --> 00:26:55,947
because he fights for his people

492
00:26:55,991 --> 00:26:59,989
and he follows a code
just like we do

493
00:27:00,033 --> 00:27:04,031
but not the soldiers
of the Dominion

494
00:27:04,076 --> 00:27:06,570
not the Jem'Hadar.

495
00:27:06,615 --> 00:27:10,111
No. They don't fight
for anything.

496
00:27:10,155 --> 00:27:13,686
They fight because they're
designed that way

497
00:27:13,796 --> 00:27:16,597
because they're programmed
to fight.

498
00:27:16,637 --> 00:27:20,202
They have no honor.

499
00:27:20,244 --> 00:27:21,543
You're right.

500
00:27:21,581 --> 00:27:24,611
That's why they're
better than us.

501
00:27:24,654 --> 00:27:25,713
That's enough.

502
00:27:25,757 --> 00:27:27,727
You're on duty in an hour,
and you...

503
00:27:27,761 --> 00:27:30,062
Ah, the Trill doesn't want you
to know the truth

504
00:27:30,099 --> 00:27:32,035
my young friend

505
00:27:32,070 --> 00:27:36,512
but you deserve to know...
the Jem'Hadar are smarter

506
00:27:36,546 --> 00:27:39,040
they're faster

507
00:27:39,086 --> 00:27:40,680
and they're stronger
than we are.

508
00:27:40,722 --> 00:27:42,749
How can you say these things?!

509
00:27:42,860 --> 00:27:43,759
He's drunk.

510
00:27:43,862 --> 00:27:44,761
Ignore him.

511
00:27:44,864 --> 00:27:46,925
No! You listen!

512
00:27:46,969 --> 00:27:49,406
Listen
and maybe learn something!

513
00:27:49,442 --> 00:27:53,109
The Jem'Hadar are the future!

514
00:27:53,149 --> 00:27:54,550
Shut up, Leskit.

515
00:27:54,586 --> 00:27:56,488
You know why?

516
00:27:56,523 --> 00:27:59,359
Because they can break us.

517
00:27:59,397 --> 00:28:02,893
Just like they broke Martok.

518
00:28:02,938 --> 00:28:04,065
That's enough!

519
00:28:04,108 --> 00:28:06,375
She doesn't want you
to know the truth.

520
00:28:06,412 --> 00:28:09,385
Martok fears them.

521
00:28:09,419 --> 00:28:13,224
That's why
we didn't attack them.

522
00:28:13,260 --> 00:28:15,127
Martok fears them!

523
00:28:39,351 --> 00:28:41,447
Dax. Dax?

524
00:28:41,489 --> 00:28:42,788
What happened?

525
00:28:42,826 --> 00:28:44,125
Are you all right?

526
00:28:44,162 --> 00:28:45,791
I had to take Ortakin
to surgery.

527
00:28:45,833 --> 00:28:47,302
Kornan almost killed him.

528
00:28:47,335 --> 00:28:48,634
Why?

529
00:28:48,672 --> 00:28:50,039
Because Leskit was drunk.

530
00:28:50,075 --> 00:28:51,236
I do not understand.

531
00:28:51,277 --> 00:28:52,404
No, you don't understand

532
00:28:52,446 --> 00:28:54,143
because you're
too busy worrying

533
00:28:54,184 --> 00:28:56,712
about Martok
while the crew is falling apart.

534
00:28:58,961 --> 00:29:02,594
Kornan needed to attack someone
and he lost control

535
00:29:02,636 --> 00:29:04,800
but this is only the beginning.

536
00:29:04,907 --> 00:29:07,777
This crew has lost half
a dozen separate actions

537
00:29:07,814 --> 00:29:08,941
to the Jem'Hadar.

538
00:29:08,983 --> 00:29:11,454
The casualty list
is as long as my arm

539
00:29:11,488 --> 00:29:13,618
and now they're
serving under a man

540
00:29:13,660 --> 00:29:15,790
who seems to have
left more behind

541
00:29:15,831 --> 00:29:17,698
than just an eye
in that prison camp.

542
00:29:17,736 --> 00:29:19,535
Do not speak of the Captain
in that manner.

543
00:29:19,573 --> 00:29:20,802
Not while I am First Officer.

544
00:29:20,842 --> 00:29:24,613
Look, I like Martok

545
00:29:24,651 --> 00:29:27,122
but this crew needs a leader

546
00:29:27,156 --> 00:29:29,491
someone who'll remind
them of their duty

547
00:29:29,528 --> 00:29:31,293
as soldiers of the Empire

548
00:29:31,332 --> 00:29:34,362
and they need that leader
right now

549
00:29:34,406 --> 00:29:36,308
or I promise you,
they will explode.

550
00:29:36,343 --> 00:29:38,336
It will not come to that!

551
00:29:40,085 --> 00:29:42,249
I know Martok.

552
00:29:42,289 --> 00:29:44,350
He is a great man.

553
00:29:44,394 --> 00:29:47,697
He will not fail us,
but we must give him time.

554
00:29:47,735 --> 00:29:50,502
Time may be the one thing
we don't have, Worf.

555
00:29:50,541 --> 00:29:54,242
What happened in that mess hall
could happen all over this ship

556
00:29:54,283 --> 00:29:57,814
and if you think the blood
looks bad on my uniform

557
00:29:57,857 --> 00:30:01,696
wait until the decks
are dripping with it.

558
00:30:14,527 --> 00:30:17,158
Commander, I'm picking up
a Klingon distress call.

559
00:30:17,199 --> 00:30:19,670
It's very faint,
but I might be able to...

560
00:30:19,705 --> 00:30:21,265
It's the <i>B'Moth.</i>

561
00:30:22,645 --> 00:30:24,809
They were attacked...

562
00:30:24,849 --> 00:30:26,945
by the Jem'Hadar
and lost main power.

563
00:30:26,988 --> 00:30:29,357
Heavy casualties.

564
00:30:29,393 --> 00:30:31,192
At least 30 survivors.

565
00:30:31,230 --> 00:30:32,824
In need of assistance.

566
00:30:32,867 --> 00:30:34,234
Emergency power's failing.

567
00:30:34,270 --> 00:30:35,329
The message repeats.

568
00:30:35,373 --> 00:30:36,899
Location?

569
00:30:36,943 --> 00:30:40,850
The signal is coming
from 055 mark 342.

570
00:30:40,884 --> 00:30:42,011
Distance...

571
00:30:42,054 --> 00:30:43,819
at least seven light years.

572
00:30:43,858 --> 00:30:47,799
Helm, alter course
to 055 mark 342.

573
00:30:47,834 --> 00:30:49,770
Understood.

574
00:30:49,804 --> 00:30:51,364
I will inform the General.

575
00:30:51,408 --> 00:30:53,275
Engineer, you have the Bridge.

576
00:31:03,467 --> 00:31:05,938
I want to thank you
for what you did

577
00:31:05,973 --> 00:31:07,442
in the mess hall.

578
00:31:07,476 --> 00:31:09,469
Is Ortakin your <i>parmach'kai?</i>

579
00:31:11,485 --> 00:31:14,515
Things are coming
to a head on this ship.

580
00:31:14,559 --> 00:31:17,794
When the fighting breaks
out, stay with me.

581
00:31:17,833 --> 00:31:19,632
I'll protect you.

582
00:31:19,670 --> 00:31:23,075
I was still hoping there wasn't
going to be any fighting.

583
00:31:35,705 --> 00:31:37,038
Station.

584
00:31:40,983 --> 00:31:41,973
Station!

585
00:31:57,319 --> 00:31:59,483
Something is wrong here, Worf.

586
00:31:59,524 --> 00:32:00,993
I can feel it.

587
00:32:01,027 --> 00:32:03,294
If the <i>B'Moth</i> was attacked
by the Jem'Hadar

588
00:32:03,332 --> 00:32:05,063
why would there be survivors?

589
00:32:05,103 --> 00:32:07,438
Since we do not know
any details of the battles

590
00:32:07,475 --> 00:32:08,699
it is difficult to speculate.

591
00:32:08,833 --> 00:32:11,897
We both know the Jem'Hadar do
not leave a task half-finished.

592
00:32:11,940 --> 00:32:15,175
If they left the ship intact
and part of the crew still alive

593
00:32:15,213 --> 00:32:16,773
they did it for a reason.

594
00:32:16,817 --> 00:32:18,480
There could be
many explanations.

595
00:32:18,521 --> 00:32:20,719
The <i>B'Moth</i> could have
inflicted heavy damage

596
00:32:20,759 --> 00:32:23,253
on the Jem'Hadar ships,
forcing them to withdraw.

597
00:32:23,298 --> 00:32:24,892
The Jem'Hadar could
have been recalled...

598
00:32:24,935 --> 00:32:27,099
How is it
that I have only one eye

599
00:32:27,140 --> 00:32:30,010
but I can see more clearly
than anyone around me?

600
00:32:30,046 --> 00:32:32,779
They deliberately left survivors
on that ship.

601
00:32:32,820 --> 00:32:34,289
Why?

602
00:32:34,322 --> 00:32:37,352
Because they want someone
to try to rescue them.

603
00:32:37,396 --> 00:32:41,360
Oh, do not take this personally,
my friend.

604
00:32:41,405 --> 00:32:43,398
I spent two years
with the Jem'Hadar.

605
00:32:43,442 --> 00:32:47,383
I do not expect you to have
the same insight into them

606
00:32:47,418 --> 00:32:50,151
that I do.

607
00:32:50,190 --> 00:32:53,493
They're soulless creatures,
Worf.

608
00:32:53,531 --> 00:32:58,907
Fighting for no goal, no purpose
except to serve the Founders.

609
00:32:58,943 --> 00:33:01,574
They take no pleasure
in what they do.

610
00:33:01,649 --> 00:33:04,519
Nothing is glorified,
nothing affirmed.

611
00:33:04,556 --> 00:33:06,185
To the Jem'Hadar

612
00:33:06,226 --> 00:33:09,130
we are nothing more than...
than targets to be destroyed.

613
00:33:09,165 --> 00:33:11,568
I must not let them
destroy us, Worf...

614
00:33:11,604 --> 00:33:13,471
With all due respect, General

615
00:33:13,508 --> 00:33:17,415
we do not know the tactical
situation of the <i>B'Moth</i> yet.

616
00:33:17,450 --> 00:33:21,391
We should guard against making
any premature judgments.

617
00:33:23,263 --> 00:33:24,926
Of course.

618
00:33:36,292 --> 00:33:37,784
Dismissed.

619
00:33:49,621 --> 00:33:51,181
<i>Rotarran</i> Combat Log

620
00:33:51,225 --> 00:33:54,960
the 53rd day in the year
of Kahless 999.

621
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,833
We have reached
the Cardassian border

622
00:33:56,870 --> 00:34:00,002
and begun our search
for the <i>B'Moth.</i>

623
00:34:00,044 --> 00:34:02,811
Helm... keep us at least

624
00:34:02,850 --> 00:34:05,344
five million <i>kellicams</i>
from the border.

625
00:34:05,390 --> 00:34:06,654
Understood.

626
00:34:06,759 --> 00:34:08,353
I think I've got something.

627
00:34:08,396 --> 00:34:10,492
It's hard to make out
through all the interference

628
00:34:10,534 --> 00:34:12,470
but the thermal signature
looks like a ship.

629
00:34:12,505 --> 00:34:14,840
It's bearing direct
to starboard

630
00:34:14,877 --> 00:34:17,474
at an elevation of 25 degrees.

631
00:34:17,516 --> 00:34:19,008
It's coming into visual range.

632
00:34:19,053 --> 00:34:20,784
On screen.

633
00:34:30,878 --> 00:34:32,677
The <i>B'Moth.</i>

634
00:34:32,715 --> 00:34:33,979
Confirmed.

635
00:34:34,019 --> 00:34:36,513
Helm, lay in a course
to bring us alongside.

636
00:34:36,558 --> 00:34:39,257
Bridge to Medical Ward.
Prepare to receive casualties.

637
00:34:39,297 --> 00:34:41,199
Assemble an armed boarding party
in Transporter Room 1.

638
00:34:41,234 --> 00:34:43,728
Make a complete search
of all the habitable areas...

639
00:34:43,807 --> 00:34:44,934
Hold.

640
00:34:44,976 --> 00:34:46,445
Commander Dax

641
00:34:46,480 --> 00:34:48,849
what side of the border
are they on?

642
00:34:48,885 --> 00:34:52,758
They're 500,000 <i>kellicams</i> inside
Cardassian territory, sir.

643
00:34:52,860 --> 00:34:55,559
They must have drifted across
a couple of days ago.

644
00:34:55,600 --> 00:34:59,507
There are probably
five Jem'Hadar warships

645
00:34:59,541 --> 00:35:01,340
out there right now

646
00:35:01,379 --> 00:35:03,873
just waiting for us
to cross the border.

647
00:35:03,918 --> 00:35:06,891
General, if they are nearby

648
00:35:06,924 --> 00:35:09,521
they do not care what side
of the border we are on.

649
00:35:09,563 --> 00:35:10,964
They will simply attack.

650
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:12,993
I have explicit orders
from the High Council

651
00:35:13,038 --> 00:35:14,735
not to enter
Cardassian territory.

652
00:35:14,775 --> 00:35:16,142
I am certain the High Council

653
00:35:16,178 --> 00:35:18,171
will not object
under these circumstances.

654
00:35:18,216 --> 00:35:19,947
There are still survivors
aboard the B'Moth.

655
00:35:19,986 --> 00:35:21,580
We do not know that.

656
00:35:21,623 --> 00:35:24,094
All that we know is there is
an automated distress call.

657
00:35:24,129 --> 00:35:25,496
They could all be dead by now.

658
00:35:25,532 --> 00:35:27,502
And if they are not?

659
00:35:29,340 --> 00:35:32,472
Then there is nothing
we can do for them.

660
00:35:32,514 --> 00:35:37,150
General, you don't intend
to just leave them there?

661
00:35:37,191 --> 00:35:39,958
I will not throw away
the lives of this crew

662
00:35:39,997 --> 00:35:42,468
in a futile rescue attempt.

663
00:35:42,502 --> 00:35:43,801
They are Klingon warriors.

664
00:35:43,839 --> 00:35:44,807
We just cannot sit...

665
00:35:44,874 --> 00:35:46,366
I have made my decision!

666
00:35:46,411 --> 00:35:49,042
We will not cross the border!

667
00:35:51,689 --> 00:35:56,359
From this moment, anyone
who questions that... - anyone...

668
00:35:56,400 --> 00:35:59,567
will be charged
with treasonable disobedience.

669
00:36:02,012 --> 00:36:04,005
Worf...

670
00:36:04,050 --> 00:36:06,248
you have the Bridge.

671
00:36:20,519 --> 00:36:21,714
Stations!

672
00:36:26,633 --> 00:36:28,626
Stations!

673
00:36:33,314 --> 00:36:35,547
We can't just leave those
men out there to die.

674
00:36:35,586 --> 00:36:37,078
No.

675
00:36:37,122 --> 00:36:38,853
So what are you going to do?

676
00:36:38,960 --> 00:36:40,623
The only thing I can do...

677
00:36:40,664 --> 00:36:43,534
challenge Martok
for command of the ship.

678
00:36:43,570 --> 00:36:45,563
I agree.

679
00:36:45,608 --> 00:36:49,013
But you realize, he may
not step aside willingly.

680
00:36:49,049 --> 00:36:50,746
I know.

681
00:36:50,786 --> 00:36:53,553
But if the General
will not step aside...

682
00:36:55,897 --> 00:36:57,958
I will have to kill him.

683
00:37:29,571 --> 00:37:32,703
Martok must die.

684
00:37:32,744 --> 00:37:34,714
That is not your decision.

685
00:37:34,748 --> 00:37:36,912
He is a coward.

686
00:37:36,987 --> 00:37:41,053
While he commands,
he dishonors us all.

687
00:37:41,096 --> 00:37:44,831
I shed no tears
for your dishonor, Leskit.

688
00:37:44,872 --> 00:37:49,405
Today would be a bad day to die

689
00:37:49,448 --> 00:37:51,077
son of Mogh.

690
00:37:51,118 --> 00:37:54,387
Take your Trill and go.

691
00:38:00,773 --> 00:38:02,367
Unlikely.

692
00:38:02,410 --> 00:38:07,012
I was hoping you would say
something like that.

693
00:38:15,305 --> 00:38:17,138
Alert Status One.

694
00:38:17,175 --> 00:38:19,669
All hands to battle stations.

695
00:38:19,714 --> 00:38:22,618
We are going to rescue
the survivors of the <i>B'Moth.</i>

696
00:38:26,863 --> 00:38:29,630
Who gave the order?

697
00:38:29,669 --> 00:38:31,639
What's going on here?

698
00:38:31,674 --> 00:38:32,835
As First Officer

699
00:38:32,876 --> 00:38:35,279
I say that you are unfit
to serve as Captain.

700
00:38:35,315 --> 00:38:37,182
You what?

701
00:38:37,219 --> 00:38:39,986
You are a coward

702
00:38:40,059 --> 00:38:42,530
and I challenge you
for command of this ship.

703
00:38:42,565 --> 00:38:46,836
I never would have expected
this from you, Worf.

704
00:39:54,823 --> 00:40:00,427
Martok, Martok,
Martok, Martok...

705
00:40:02,195 --> 00:40:05,966
Tactical alert!
Tactical alert!

706
00:40:06,004 --> 00:40:09,705
There is a Jem'Hadar warship
bearing 180 mark 215.

707
00:40:09,745 --> 00:40:13,150
They will be within weapons
range in nine minutes.

708
00:40:14,623 --> 00:40:19,225
The Jem'Hadar will soon learn
to regret this day.

709
00:40:19,267 --> 00:40:21,237
Who is with me?!

710
00:40:21,271 --> 00:40:22,330
Tavana!

711
00:40:22,373 --> 00:40:26,508
Sometimes... I think
I know why I love you.

712
00:40:26,549 --> 00:40:28,314
Let's go to the Medical Ward.

713
00:40:28,353 --> 00:40:29,480
Shields and weapons ready.

714
00:40:29,522 --> 00:40:30,490
