00:41:27,750 --> 00:41:29,117
How's the intelligence
business?

738
00:41:29,153 --> 00:41:30,554
Oh, I can't talk about it.

739
00:41:30,589 --> 00:41:32,354
All I can do is read
these fascinating reports

740
00:41:32,393 --> 00:41:34,090
and analyses,
and analyses of analyses

741
00:41:34,130 --> 00:41:35,463
and then
keep it all to myself

742
00:41:35,500 --> 00:41:37,767
because no one else
has "a need to know."

743
00:41:37,806 --> 00:41:39,070
So I have to walk
around this station

744
00:41:39,108 --> 00:41:40,668
feeling like I, uh...

745
00:41:40,712 --> 00:41:42,045
You don't really care,
do you?

746
00:41:42,082 --> 00:41:43,311
No.

747
00:41:44,887 --> 00:41:47,757
A vessel's de-cloaking 15
kilometers off the station.

748
00:41:47,794 --> 00:41:49,161
It's the <i>Rotarran.</i>

749
00:41:49,197 --> 00:41:50,426
Martok's ship.

750
00:41:50,467 --> 00:41:52,164
Yes, sir, and there's
an incoming transmission.

751
00:41:52,204 --> 00:41:54,368
On screen.

752
00:41:54,409 --> 00:41:56,379
Major, we've rescued
35 survivors

753
00:41:56,413 --> 00:41:58,509
of a disabled
Klingon battle cruiser.

754
00:41:58,551 --> 00:42:01,615
Request permission to beam them
directly to your Infirmary.

755
00:42:01,657 --> 00:42:03,422
Permission granted, General.

756
00:42:03,462 --> 00:42:05,364
You're also cleared
to dock at Bay 4.

757
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:07,199
We'll need an engineering team

758
00:42:07,237 --> 00:42:10,699
to repair our battle damage,
and one other thing.

759
00:42:10,744 --> 00:42:12,908
Arrange to have
15 barrels of bloodwine

760
00:42:13,016 --> 00:42:14,451
waiting for us at the airlock

761
00:42:14,486 --> 00:42:17,789
so that we can celebrate
the first victory

762
00:42:17,827 --> 00:42:21,768
of the <i>Rotarran</i>
over the Jem'Hadar!

763
00:42:34,129 --> 00:42:35,723
Worf.

764
00:42:35,766 --> 00:42:37,133
General.

765
00:42:37,169 --> 00:42:40,472
The High Council
has issued a commendation

766
00:42:40,510 --> 00:42:43,311
for the entire crew
of the <i>Rotarran.</i>

767
00:42:43,349 --> 00:42:45,980
It would seem
that you were right.

768
00:42:46,022 --> 00:42:48,493
They view the destruction
of a Jem'Hadar ship

769
00:42:48,528 --> 00:42:52,229
and the rescue of 35 warriors
as ample justification

770
00:42:52,269 --> 00:42:53,966
for crossing
the Cardassian border.

771
00:42:54,006 --> 00:42:58,380
Your... actions
on the <i>Rotarran...</i>

772
00:42:58,415 --> 00:43:00,648
at the time,
I thought they were disloyal

773
00:43:00,687 --> 00:43:03,158
but I have come to realize

774
00:43:03,193 --> 00:43:05,664
that your intention
was to remind me of my duty

775
00:43:05,698 --> 00:43:08,101
as a soldier of the Empire
and as a warrior.

776
00:43:08,137 --> 00:43:09,436
For that, I am grateful.

777
00:43:09,474 --> 00:43:11,273
You did the same for me once.

778
00:43:11,311 --> 00:43:12,837
Worf...

779
00:43:14,418 --> 00:43:18,985
on the Bridge, during the fight
when you dropped your guard

780
00:43:19,061 --> 00:43:22,034
how did you know
I would not kill you?

781
00:43:26,678 --> 00:43:28,272
I did not know.

782
00:43:31,990 --> 00:43:33,425
I see you're still wearing

783
00:43:33,459 --> 00:43:35,156
the crest
of the House of Mogh.

784
00:43:38,303 --> 00:43:39,829
Yes.

785
00:43:39,873 --> 00:43:43,678
Jadzia calls it
a... sentimental gesture.

786
00:43:43,716 --> 00:43:44,980
Ah.

787
00:43:45,018 --> 00:43:49,620
Perhaps you would consider
replacing sentiment with...

788
00:43:49,662 --> 00:43:52,635
the symbol of a new beginning.

789
00:43:55,408 --> 00:44:00,818
The House of Martok
would be honored

790
00:44:00,853 --> 00:44:03,849
to welcome the son of Mogh
into our family

791
00:44:03,893 --> 00:44:06,660
as a warrior...

792
00:44:06,699 --> 00:44:07,921
and as a brother.

793
00:44:25,126 --> 00:44:27,119
<i>- Qapla'!</i>
<i>- Qapla'!</i>

